The '''Omicron Centaurids''' [[meteor shower]] has a [[radiant (meteor shower)|radiant]] which is in the constellation [[Centaurus]] which is visible from the southern hemisphere.<ref name=imo>Lunsford, Robert, [http://www.imo.net/node/924 International Meteor Organization], February 18, 2006. Retrieved January 21, 2007</ref> It is most easily seen at 2:00 am, local standard time.<ref name=imo/> It is visible from late January through February each year.<ref name=imo/> It peaks in mid-February.<ref name=imo/>

