{{Multiple issues|{{more citations needed|date=November 2017}}{{notability|date=November 2017}}}} The '''Joan Gerard Youth Awards''' were established in 1989 by the [[World Bridge Federation]] to celebrate the sportsmanship of competitive youth [[contract bridge]] players. They were originally called the '''WBF Youth Award''' and were awarded biennially to four competitive bridge players under the age of 26. From 1995 to 2006, this coincided with the World Junior Camp.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldbridge.org/competitions/the-other-wbf-events/world-junior-camp/|title=The World Junior Camp - World Bridge Federation|website=www.worldbridge.org|accessdate=25 February 2018}}</ref> They were discontinued in 2007 at the same time as the discontinuation of the camps but reinstated in 2013 in a new form, being awarded annually at the [[World Junior Teams Championship|Youth Bridge Teams Championships]] to a Junior, a Youngster, a Girl, and starting in 2015, a Kid. After the passing of Joan Gerard, they were renamed in her memory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://youth.worldbridge.org/the-wbf-youth-awards/|title=The WBF Youth Awards - Youth World Bridge|website=youth.worldbridge.org|accessdate=25 February 2018}}</ref>
